CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*dev)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct cpuidle_device)...)
#113: FILE: drivers/cpuidle/cpuidle.c:129:
+		dev = kzalloc(sizeof(struct cpuidle_device), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

ERROR:INLINE_LOCATION: inline keyword should sit between storage class and type
#208: FILE: drivers/cpuidle/sysfs.c:290:
+static void inline cpuidle_free_state_kobj(struct cpuidle_device *device, int i)

The inline keyword should sit between storage class and type.

For example, the following segment::

  inline static int example_function(void)
  {
          ...
  }

should be::

  static inline int example_function(void)
  {
          ...
  }

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*kobj)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct cpuidle_state_kobj)...)
#234: FILE: drivers/cpuidle/sysfs.c:309:
+		kobj = kzalloc(sizeof(struct cpuidle_state_kobj), GFP_KERNEL);

